# TiltyTable Arcade — Open Sauce

We are building a **fun physical interactive arcade game for Open Sauce** on
TiltyTable hardware: real servo-actuated tiles, LEDs, Stewart tilt, roller-ball
input, scored gauntlet/practice levels, and synthesized cabinet audio. The
`arcade/` stack ties game logic, hardware adapters, and the cabinet display
together.

## Cabinet UI copy (hard requirement)

The 854×480 projector kiosk is player-facing — not a marketing page, product
demo, developer console, or hardware dashboard.

- Every visible word must help the player understand the current state or take
  the next action.
- Use short commands, essential game rules, timer/score labels, and clear
  results.
- Do not show implementation details, device paths, hardware jargon, developer
  terminology, future integrations, diagnostics, or calibration details.
- Do not add slogans, promotional claims, decorative subheadings, tile-count
  branding, or helper copy that repeats an on-screen action.
- Use `TILTYTABLE` as the title unless the project establishes a real game name.
- Keep level instructions limited to the immediate mechanic; explain ball
  placement on the placement screen.
- Optimize every state for immediate legibility at 854×480 from cabinet
  viewing distance.
- Preserve the old-school arcade visual style without using extra copy as
  decoration.
